(This fictional city brief was created for teaching RAG retrieval and evaluation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This fictional glossary supports comparison across the Rivergate, Sunford, Lakemont, and) Tj
T*
(Northbridge adaptation briefs. It defines recurring terms that students may encounter when) Tj
T*
(evaluating retrieval results. The glossary is not a complete climate textbook. It is a compact) Tj
T*
(reference for the exercise.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Climate adaptation means changing systems so they can handle climate impacts that are already) Tj
T*
(happening or likely to happen. Flood barriers, cooling centers, green roofs, and backup bus) Tj
T*
(routes are adaptation measures. Climate mitigation means reducing the causes of climate) Tj
T*
(change, for example by lowering greenhouse gas emissions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Heat mitigation and heat response are related but different. Heat mitigation reduces heat) Tj
T*
(before an emergency, such as shade trees, cool roofs, and reflective surfaces. Heat response) Tj
T*
(protects people during an active heat event, such as cooling centers, water distribution, and) Tj
T*
(wellness checks.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Nature-based solutions use natural processes to reduce risk. Rivergate's wetland restoration,) Tj
T*
(Sunford's shade trees, and Lakemont's rain gardens are examples. Nature-based solutions can) Tj
T*
(provide extra benefits such as cleaner water, habitat, and cooler streets, but they still) Tj
T*
(require maintenance and monitoring.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Social vulnerability describes how climate risk is shaped by age, income, disability, health,) Tj
T*
(housing, language access, and transport options. A flood warning is less useful if a resident) Tj
T*
(cannot leave without help. A heat alert is less useful if a worker cannot change schedule or) Tj
T*
(reach a cooling center.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Resilience does not mean that nothing fails. In these briefs, resilience means that failures) Tj
T*
(are less likely, warnings arrive earlier, damage is smaller, and recovery is faster.) Tj
T*
(Northbridge may still lose tram service during a severe storm, but backup route B-12 can keep) Tj
T*
(essential trips moving.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Evaluation questions should usually name an expected source. A flood question is often) Tj
T*
(answered by Rivergate. A heat-health question is often answered by Sunford. A green roof or) Tj
T*
(permeable pavement question is often answered by Lakemont. A transport disruption question is) Tj
T*
(often answered by Northbridge. A definition question is often answered by this glossary.) Tj
